<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. ruah" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" rank="species" species="ruah">P. ruah</taxonomicName>
was recorded for the first time on marginal rocks of a small stream, at 2575 m a.s.l. (
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="-22.428055">22°25'41&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="-44.843887">44°50'38&quot;W</geoCoordinate>
), in APASM (Minas Gerais State). Larva, pupa, female and male have been described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shimabukuro, EM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" pagination="134 - 154" title="Brazilian Pseudochironomini (Diptera: Chironomidae) Part 1. New Pseudochironomus Malloch from highlands." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4317.1.6" volume="4317" year="2017 a">Shimabukuro et al. (2017a)</bibRefCitation>
. Environmental characterization: Water temperature 22 °C; dissolved oxygen 7.4 mg.l-1; pH 5.5; fast flowing; vegetal canopy absent. High altitudinal specificity (IndVal: 0.67; p = 0.003).
</paragraph>
